title: how to downsample a jpeg
pid: 98678545-49c1-4af1-a59b-001ef951a6c8
body: |2-
    First check its dimensions with `file`.
    Then choose new dimensions, and run
    `magick convert input.jpg -resize 600x400\> output.jpg`
  #+BEGIN_SRC bash
  for i in *.jpg; do
    magick convert $i -resize 1020x765\> $i.small.jpg
  done
  #+END_SRC
